gebra/Basic.html#AlgHom.range\">range</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Subalgebra/Lattice.html#Algebra.adjoin\">Algebra.adjoin</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Basic.html#AlgHom.fieldRange\">fieldRange</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Adjoin/Defs.html#IntermediateField.adjoin\">IntermediateField.adjoin</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `F` is a field, `A` is an `F`-algebra with fraction field `K`, `L` is a field,\n`g : A →ₐ[F] L` lifts to `f : K →ₐ[F] L`,\n`s` is a set such that the image of `g` is the subalgebra generated by `s`,\nthen the image of `f` is the intermediate field generated by `s`.\nNote: this does not require `IsScalarTower F A K`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Adjoin/Algebra.html#IsFractionRing.algHom_fieldRange_eq_of_comp_eq_of_range_eq","kind":"theorem","line":340,"name":"IsFractionRing.algHom_fieldRange_eq_of_comp_eq_of_range_eq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Adjoin/Algebra.lean#L340-L352"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Adjoin/Algebra.html#IsFractionRing.algHom_fieldRange_eq_of_comp_eq\"><span class=\"name\">IsFractionRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">algHom_fieldRange_eq_of_comp_eq</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">